ACDE is a research-grade and production tool for policy-bounded agentic governance of
cloud data pipelines. It originated as an open replication of and extension to:

  "Governing Cloud Data Pipelines with Agentic AI" (arXiv:2512.23737),
  Kirubakaran et al., 2025.

ACDE is an independent implementation and is not affiliated with or endorsed by the
paper's authors or their institutions.

Third-party data sources used by the optional research/benchmark components are described
in DATA_LICENSES.md (TPC-DS is a trademark of the TPC; NYC TLC trip data is public data of
the City of New York). ACDE ships none of that data; it is generated or fetched on demand.

THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND. ACDE proposes and (when
configured to do so) executes operational actions against data pipelines; operators are
responsible for reviewing policies, choosing an execution mode, and validating behavior in
a non-production environment before granting write access to production systems.
